02Ex 22:1 "If a man steals an ox or sheep and slaughters it or sells it, he shall repay five oxen for the ox and four sheep for the sheep.
02Ex 22:2 "If a thief is found while breaking into a house, and is struck down and dies, it is not a capital crime in that case, 
02Ex 22:3 but if the sun has risen on him, then it is a capital crime in that case. "A thief shall surely make restitution, but if he has nothing, he shall be sold for his theft. 
02Ex 22:4 If what was stolen is actually found alive in his possession, whether an ox, a donkey or a sheep, he shall repay double.
02Ex 22:5 "When a man lets a field or vineyard be grazed over or releases his livestock so that they graze in another man's field, he shall make restitution from the best of his field or vineyard.
02Ex 22:6 "When a fire breaks out and spreads into thorn bushes and consumes stacked grain or standing grain or the field, the one who started the fire shall surely make restitution.
02Ex 22:7 "When a man gives his neighbor money or goods for safekeeping and it's stolen from the neighbor's house, the thief, if found, shall repay double. 
02Ex 22:8 If the thief is not found, the owner of the house shall appear before the judges to see whether or not the thief took his neighbor's property.
02Ex 22:9 "In every ownership dispute involving an ox, donkey, sheep, garment, or anything that is lost where a person says, 'This is mine,' the case between the two of them shall come before the judges, and the one that the judges declare guilty shall repay double to his neighbor.
02Ex 22:10 "When a man gives a donkey or ox or sheep or any animal to his neighbor for safe keeping, and it dies or is injured or is driven away when no one is looking, 
02Ex 22:11 the two of them shall take an oath in the Lord's presence that the accused has not taken his neighbor's property. Its owner shall accept this, and the neighbor shall not make restitution. 
02Ex 22:12 But if it was actually stolen from him, the neighbor shall make restitution to its owner. 
02Ex 22:13 If it was torn to pieces, let the neighbor bring the remains as evidence, and he shall not make restitution for what was torn apart.
02Ex 22:14 "When a man borrows an animal from his neighbor, and it's injured or dies while its owner was not with it, he shall surely make restitution. 
02Ex 22:15 If its owner was with it, he shall not make restitution. If it was hired, its fee covers the loss."
02Ex 22:16 "When a man seduces a virgin who is not engaged to be married and lies with her, he must pay her bride-price, and she becomes his wife. 
02Ex 22:17 If her father absolutely refuses to give her to him, he shall pay an amount equal to the bride-price for virgins.
02Ex 22:18 "You are not to allow a sorceress to live.
02Ex 22:19 "Whoever has sexual relations with an animal shall surely be put to death.
02Ex 22:20 "Anyone who sacrifices to a god, except the Lord alone, shall be utterly destroyed.
02Ex 22:21 "You are not to wrong or oppress an alien, because you were aliens in the land of Egypt. 
02Ex 22:22 You are not to mistreat any widow or orphan. 
02Ex 22:23 If you do mistreat them, they'll surely cry out to me, and I'll immediately hear their cry. 
02Ex 22:24 And I'll be angry and will kill you with the sword, and your wives shall become widows and your children orphans.
02Ex 22:25 "If you loan money to my people, to the poor among you, don't be like a creditor to them and don't impose interest on them. 
02Ex 22:26 If you take your neighbor's coat as collateral, you are to return it to him by sunset, 
02Ex 22:27 for it's his only covering; it's his outer garment, for what else can he sleep in -  And when he cries out to me, I'll hear him, for I am gracious.22
02Ex 22:28 "You are not to blaspheme God or curse a ruler of your people.
02Ex 22:29 "You are not to hold back the fullness of your harvest and the outflow of your wine presses. You are to give to me the firstborn of your sons. 
02Ex 22:30 You are to do the same with your oxen and your sheep. They shall be with their mother for seven days and then on the eighth day you are to give them to me.2229
02Ex 22:31 "You are to be people set apart for me. You are not to eat flesh torn apart in the field; you are to throw it to the dogs."
02Ex 23:1 "You are not to spread a false report, nor shall you join forces with the wicked to be a malicious witness. 
02Ex 23:2 You are not to follow the majority in doing wrong, and you are not to testify in a lawsuit so as to follow the majority and pervert justice. 
02Ex 23:3 You are not to show partiality to a poor man in his lawsuit.
02Ex 23:4 "If you come across your enemy's ox or donkey wandering off, you are to certainly return it to him. 
02Ex 23:5 If you see your enemy's donkey lying helpless under its load, you must not abandon it, rather, you are to surely return it to him.
02Ex 23:6 "You are not to pervert justice for the poor among you in their lawsuits. 
02Ex 23:7 Stay far away from a false charge, and don't kill the innocent or the righteous, because I won't acquit the guilty. 
02Ex 23:8 You are not to take a bribe because a bribe blinds the clear-sighted and distorts the words of the righteous. 
02Ex 23:9 You are not to oppress the resident alien, because you were aliens in the land of Egypt.
02Ex 23:10 "You are to sow your land and gather its crops for six years, 
02Ex 23:11 but you are to let it rest the seventh year, leaving it unplanted. The poor of your people may eat from it, and the wild animals may eat what they leave. You are to do the same with your vineyards and olive groves. 
02Ex 23:12 You are to do your work for six days, but on the seventh day you are to refrain from work so that your ox and donkey may rest, and so the son of your maidservant and the alien may be refreshed. 
02Ex 23:13 "Be careful about everything I've told you, and don't mention the name of other gods. Don't let them be heard in your mouth!
02Ex 23:14 "Three times a year you are to celebrate a festival for me. 
02Ex 23:15 You are to observe the Festival of Unleavened Bread. As I commanded you, you are to eat unleavened bread for seven days at the appointed time in the month Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt. No one shall appear before me empty handed. 
02Ex 23:16 You are to observe the Festival of Harvest, celebrating the first fruits of your work in planting the field, and the Festival of Ingathering at the end of the year, when you gather the fruit of your work from the field. 
02Ex 23:17 Three times a year all your males shall appear in the presence of the Lord God."
02Ex 23:18 "You are not to offer the blood of my sacrifice with anything leavened, and you are not to let the fat portion of my sacrifice remain overnight until morning.
02Ex 23:19 "You are to bring the best of the first fruits of your soil to the house of the Lord your God. "You are not to boil a young goat in its mother's milk."
02Ex 23:20 "Look, I'm sending an angel in front of you to guard you on the way and to bring you to the place I've prepared. 
02Ex 23:21 Be careful in his presence - be sure to obey him. Don't rebel against him, for he won't forgive your transgression, since my name is in him. 
02Ex 23:22 Indeed, if you carefully obey him and do everything that I say, then I'll be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries. 
02Ex 23:23 For my angel will go ahead of you and will bring you to the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, and I'll annihilate them. 
02Ex 23:24 You are not to bow down to their gods or serve them. You are not to follow their practices, but you are to completely overthrow them and smash their sacred stones to pieces. 
02Ex 23:25 You are to serve the Lord your God, and he will bless your food and water, and I'll remove sickness from you. 
02Ex 23:26 No woman will miscarry or be barren in your land, and I'll make every day of your life complete.24
02Ex 23:27 "I'll go ahead of you and terrorize all the people to whom you are coming. I'll confuse your enemies and make them turn their backs on you and run away. 
02Ex 23:28 I'll send hornets ahead of you and they'll drive out the Hivites, the Canaanites, and the Hittites before you. 
02Ex 23:29 I won't drive them out before you in a single year, so that the land does not become desolate and so that wild do not overrun you. 
02Ex 23:30 I'll drive them out ahead of you little by little until you increase in numbers and possess the land.2328
02Ex 23:31 "I'll set your borders from the Reed Sea to the Sea of the Philistines, and from the desert to the Euphrates River, for I'll bring the inhabitants of the land under your control, and you are to drive them out ahead of you. 
02Ex 23:32 You are not to make a covenant with them or with their gods. 
02Ex 23:33 They shall not live in your land. Otherwise they will cause you to sin against me. If you worship their gods, it will become a snare for you."
02Ex 24:1 The Lord said to Moses, "Come up to the Lord, you and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel, and worship at a distance. 
02Ex 24:2 Only Moses shall approach the Lord, but the others shall not approach; the people shall not come up with him."
