03Lv 1:12 He is to cut up its head and fat into separate pieces. Then the priest is to arrange them in rows on the wood over the fire that burns on the altar. 
03Lv 1:13 Then he is to wash its entrails and legs with water. After this, the priest is to offer all of it on the altar - a burnt offering by fire, an aroma that will be pleasing to the Lord."
03Lv 1:14 "If his offering is a burnt offering of birds to the Lord, he is to bring turtledoves or young doves. 
03Lv 1:15 The priest is to bring it to the altar to offer it up in smoke. He is to decapitate it, drain its blood on the side of the altar, 
03Lv 1:16 and then he is to eviscerate it, and throw the viscera and the feathers to the east side of the altar, where the fatty ashes are located. 
03Lv 1:17 He is then to tear it open by its wings, but not dividing it completely into two parts. The priest is then to offer all of it on the wood over the fire as a burnt offering by fire, an aroma pleasing to the Lord."1
03Lv 2:1 "When a person brings an offering - that is, a grain offering to the Lord, his offering is to consist of fine flour. He is to pour olive oil mixed with frankincense over it. 
03Lv 2:2 Then he is to bring it to Aaron's sons, the priests. He is to take a handful of fine flour, the olive oil, and all of the frankincense. Then the priest is to offer a memorial offering by fire, an aroma pleasing to the Lord. 
03Lv 2:3 The remnants from the grain offering is for Aaron and his sons - the holiest of the offerings made by fire to the Lord."
03Lv 2:4 "When you bring an offering - that is, a grain offering baked in an oven, it is to consist of fine flour baked into unleavened bread mixed with olive oil or of wafers made of unleavened bread and smeared with olive oil.
03Lv 2:5 "If your grain offering has been prepared on a griddle, then it is to consist of fine flour mixed with olive oil. 
03Lv 2:6 Crumble it into morsels of bread and then pour olive oil on it. It's a grain offering. 
03Lv 2:7 "When your grain offering has been prepared in a stew pan, it is to consist of fine flour mixed with olive oil. 
03Lv 2:8 Bring the grain offering that you prepared from these ingredients to the Lord. Present it to the priest, who will bring it to the altar. 
03Lv 2:9 Then the priest will dedicate some of the grain offering as a memorial offering and offer it in smoke on the altar, an offering by fire that will be a pleasing aroma to the Lord. 
03Lv 2:10 The remainder from the memorial offering is for Aaron and his sons - the holiest of the offerings made by fire to the Lord."
03Lv 2:11 "Any grain offering that you bring to the Lord is not to be prepared with yeast, because anything with leaven and honey may not be offered in smoke as an offering by fire to the Lord. 
03Lv 2:12 You may bring them to the Lord as an offering of first-fruits, but they are not to be offered on the altar for a pleasing aroma."
03Lv 2:13 "Also, be sure to rub every offering from your grain offering with salt. You are not to ever remove the salt of the covenant of your God from your grain offering. Present all your offerings with salt."
03Lv 2:14 "Whenever you bring a grain offering of first-fruits to the Lord, bring fresh barley, roasted in fire, young kernels crushed into bits. Bring the grain offering with your first-fruits 
03Lv 2:15 and then pour olive oil and frankincense over it as a grain offering. 
03Lv 2:16 The priest is to offer the memorial offering in smoke - its crushed bits, olive oil, and frankincense - as an offering by fire to the Lord."
03Lv 3:1 "If someone's offering is a peace offering from the cattle, the presenter is to offer it without defects, whether the animal is male or female. They are to be brought to the Lord. 
03Lv 3:2 Then the presenter is to lay his hand on the head of the offering and slaughter it at the entrance of the Tent of Meeting. After this, Aaron's sons, the priests, are to sprinkle the blood on and around the altar.
03Lv 3:3 "The presenter is then to bring a gift from the peace offering, an offering made by fire to the Lord. He is to remove the fat that covers the internal organs, all of the fat that is inside the internal organs, 
03Lv 3:4 the two kidneys with the fat on them by the loins, and the fatty mass that surrounds the liver and kidneys. 
03Lv 3:5 Then Aaron's sons are to burn them on the altar, over the burnt offering that has been placed on the wood, over the fire, as an offering made by fire, an aroma pleasing to the Lord. 
03Lv 3:6 "If his offering to the Lord is a peace offering from the flock, whether male or female, he is to bring them without defect. 
03Lv 3:7 If the offering that he is bringing is a lamb, then he is to bring it to the Lord. 
03Lv 3:8 He is to lay his hand on the head of his offering and slaughter it at the entrance of the Tent of Meeting. Then Aaron's sons are to sprinkle the blood on and around the altar.
03Lv 3:9 "The presenter is then to bring a gift from the peace offering as an offering made by fire to the Lord. He is to remove the fat, the entire fat tail near the spine, the fat that covers the internal organs, all of the fat that is inside the internal organs, 
03Lv 3:10 the two kidneys with the fat on them by the loins, and the fatty mass that surrounds the liver and kidneys. 
03Lv 3:11 Then the priest is to burn them on the altar as a food offering made by fire to the Lord. 
03Lv 3:12 "If his offering is a goat, then he is to bring it to the Lord, 
03Lv 3:13 lay his hand over its head, then slaughter it at the entrance of the Tent of Meeting. After this, Aaron's sons are to sprinkle the blood on and around the altar. 
03Lv 3:14 "The presenter is then to present the gift as an offering made by fire to the Lord, that is, the fat that covers the internal organs, all the fat that is inside the internal organs, 
03Lv 3:15 the two kidneys with the fat on them by the loins, and the fatty mass that surrounds the liver and kidneys. 
03Lv 3:16 The priest is to burn them on the altar, a food offering made by fire, a pleasing aroma. All the fat belongs to the Lord.314
03Lv 3:17 "This is to be be a lasting statute for all your generations, wherever you live. You are not to eat any fat or blood. "
03Lv 4:1 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 4:2 "Speak to the Israelites and tell them, 'If a person inadvertently sins with respect to any of the Lord's commands that should not be violated, but nevertheless he disobeys one of them, 
03Lv 4:3 or if the anointed priest sins, thereby bringing guilt on the people, let him bring a young bull without defect as a sin offering to the Lord for his sin that he had committed.
03Lv 4:4 "'He is to bring the bull to the entrance of the Tent of Meeting, into the Lord's presence, where he is to lay his hand on the head of the bull and slaughter it in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 4:5 The anointed priest is to take blood from the bull to the Tent of Meeting. 
03Lv 4:6 The priest is to dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle some of the blood seven times in the Lord's presence in front of the curtain of the sanctuary.
03Lv 4:7 "'The priest is then to put some blood on the horn of the altar that is near the Tent of Meeting as an incense of pleasing aroma in the Lord's presence. He is to pour the rest of the bull's blood for a burnt offering at the base of the altar that is at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting. 
03Lv 4:8 Then he is to remove all the fat from the bull for a sin offering -  that is, the fat that covers the internal organs, all of the fat that is inside the internal organs, 
03Lv 4:9 the two kidneys with the fat on them by the loins, and the fatty mass the surrounds the liver and kidneys, 
03Lv 4:10 just as they are taken from the bull for a peace offering. Then the priest is to burn them on the altar for burnt offerings.
03Lv 4:11 "'Now as for the bull's hide, its flesh, its head, its legs, its internal organs, its dung, 
03Lv 4:12 along with the rest of the bull, he is to bring it outside the camp to a clean place, where fat ashes are to be poured over it and then it is to be thoroughly burned over wood with fire. It is to be burned where the fat ashes are poured out.'"
03Lv 4:13 "If the whole congregation of Israel goes astray, and if the sin is hidden from the eyes of the assembly, and if they will have gone astray from one of the Lord's commands that should not be violated, then they will stand guilty. 
03Lv 4:14 When the sin that they have committed becomes known, the entire congregation is to bring a young bull as a sin offering to the Tent of Meeting, 
03Lv 4:15 where the elders of the community are to lay their hands on the head of the bull in the Lord's presence and slaughter it. 
03Lv 4:16 The anointed priest is to take blood from the bull and bring it to the Tent of Meeting. 
03Lv 4:17 Then the priest is to dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle some of the blood seven times in front of the curtain in the Lord's presence.
03Lv 4:18 "Then the priest is to put blood on the horn of the altar near the Tent of Meeting in the Lord's presence. He is to pour the rest of the blood as a burnt offering at the base of the altar that is at the entrance of the Tent of Meeting. 
03Lv 4:19 Then he is to remove all the fat from the bull for a sin offering and burn it on the altar.
03Lv 4:20 "He is to do to the bull what he did to the bull for sin offering. He is to do it this way so that the priest will make atonement for them and they will be forgiven. 
03Lv 4:21 Then he is to bring the rest of the bull outside the camp and burn it just as he had burned the first bull. This is the sin offering for the congregation."
03Lv 4:22 "When a ruler inadvertently sins, disobeying any one of the commands of the Lord his God that should not be violated, he will be guilty. 
03Lv 4:23 When the sin that he had committed is disclosed to him, he is to bring his offering£º a male goat without defect. 
03Lv 4:24 He is then to lay his hand on the head of the goat and slaughter it at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered - in the Lord's presence - as a sin offering. 
03Lv 4:25 Then the priest is to take blood from the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horn of the altar that is used for burnt offerings. He is to pour the rest of the blood at the base of the altar that is used for burnt offerings. 
03Lv 4:26 But he is to burn all the fat on the altar as is done for the fat for the sacrifice of a peace offering. This is how the priest will make atonement for him concerning his sin. It will be forgiven him."
03Lv 4:27 "If any of the common people of the land inadvertently sins by disobeying one of the Lord's commands that should not be violated, he will be guilty. 
03Lv 4:28 When the sin that he committed is disclosed to him, he is to bring his offering for his sin that he had committed£º a female goat without defect. 
03Lv 4:29 He is to lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and slaughter it at the place for burnt offering. 
03Lv 4:30 Then the priest is to take blood with his finger, put it on the horn of the altar that is used for burnt offerings, and then pour the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. 
03Lv 4:31 He is to remove all the fat, just as the fat was removed from the sacrifice for peace offering. Then the priest is to burn it on the altar as a pleasing aroma to the Lord. This is how the priest will make atonement for him. It will be forgiven him. 
03Lv 4:32 "If he brings a lamb for his offering, he is to bring a female without defect. 
03Lv 4:33 He is to lay his hand on the head of the offering and slaughter it for a sin offering at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered. 
03Lv 4:34 Then the priest is to take blood with his finger and put it on the horn of the altar for burnt offering. Then he is to pour the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. 
03Lv 4:35 Then the presenter is to remove all its fat, just as the fat was removed from the sacrifice of peace offering. The priest is to burn it on the altar over the offerings made by fire to the Lord. This is how the priest will make atonement for him concerning the sin that he had committed. It will be forgiven him."434
03Lv 5:1 "If someone sins because he has received notice that he is to testify as a witness regarding what he has observed or learned, but then he fails to testify, he will be guilty.
03Lv 5:2 When a person has touched a ceremonially unclean thing inadvertently, such as the carcass of an unclean animal, or some unclean creeping thing, he will be unclean and guilty nevertheless.
03Lv 5:3 "When he inadvertently touches the uncleanness of a human being, whatever his uncleanness that made him unclean may be, when he himself comes to know about it, he will be guilty. 
03Lv 5:4 When a person has sworn inadvertently by what he has said, whether for evil or good, whatever it was that the person spoke, when he comes to understand what he said, he will incur guilt by of one of these things.
03Lv 5:5 "When a person is guilty of one of these things, then he is to confess whatever sin it was 
03Lv 5:6 and bring compensation to the Lord for the guilt that he committed£º a female from the flock - whether a lamb or goat - for a sin offering. Then the priest is to make atonement for him.
03Lv 5:7 "If he can't afford a goat, then he is to bring for his sin offering two turtledoves or two young doves to the Lord£º one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. 
03Lv 5:8 He is to bring them to the priest, who will offer a sin offering first. He is to wring off its head without separating it. 
03Lv 5:9 Then he is to spatter some of the blood from the sin offering on the sidewall of the altar. Now as to the remainder of the blood, he is to pour it out at the base of the altar for a sin offering.
03Lv 5:10 "Now as to the second, he is to prepare it as a burnt offering according to the approved procedure. The priest is to make atonement for him on account of his sin that he had committed. Then it will be forgiven him. 
03Lv 5:11 "If he can't afford two turtledoves or two young doves, then he is to bring as his offering a tenth of an ephah of fine flour as a sin offering for what he has committed. He is to put no olive oil or frankincense on it, since it's a sin offering. 
03Lv 5:12 He is to bring it to the priest. The priest is to take a handful as a memorial and burn it on the altar as an offering made by fire to the Lord. It's a sin offering. 
03Lv 5:13 The priest will make atonement for him, on account of the sin that he had committed in any of these things and it will forgiven him. As far as the priest is concerned, it will be a meal offering."
03Lv 5:14 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 5:15 "When a person commits a truly treacherous act and sins inadvertently concerning the sacred things of the Lord, then he is to bring a trespass offering from the flock to the Lord as compensation for his guilt. It is to be a ram without defect, estimated as to its value in silver shekels, according to the sanctuary shekel. 
03Lv 5:16 He is to compensate for whatever sin he had committed concerning the sacred things of the Lord, add a fifth part to it, and give it to the priest. The priest is to make atonement for him with the ram as a sin offering and he'll be forgiven.
03Lv 5:17 "If a person sins and does what the Lord commanded is not to be done, and if he didn't know that he had sinned, then he will be guilty nevertheless. 
03Lv 5:18 He is to bring to the priest from the flock a ram without defect, estimated as to its value in silver shekels, as a guilt offering. Then the priest is to make atonement for him concerning his inadvertent act that he committed through ignorance, and it will be forgiven him. 19It's a sin offering for his guilt in the Lord's presence."
03Lv 6:1 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 6:2 "A person sins against the Lord by acting treacherously toward his neighbor regarding something entrusted to his care, security for a loan, robbery, or if he has oppressed his neighbor, 
03Lv 6:3 found something that had been lost and then lied about it, or if he makes a false oath about any of these things, thus commiting a sin with respect to these things.
03Lv 6:4 "If that person has sinned and has been found guilty, then he is to return the stolen thing that he took or obtained by oppression, or the security that had been entrusted to him, or the lost thing that he had found, 
03Lv 6:5 or the thing about which he had given a false oath. He is to restore it in full, add a fifth to it, then give to whom it belongs the very day he's found guilty.
03Lv 6:6 "Now as to his guilt offering, he is to bring to the Lord a ram without defect from the flock, estimated as to its value, to the priest. 
03Lv 6:7 Then the priest is to make atonement for him in the Lord's presence, and it will be forgiven him regarding whatever he did. 
03Lv 6:8 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 6:9 "Deliver these orders to Aaron and his sons concerning the regulations for burnt offerings. The burnt offering is to remain on the hearth of the altar throughout the entire night until morning, and the fire on the altar is to be kept burning along with it.
03Lv 6:10 "The priest is to clothe himself with linen robe and underclothes. Then he is to take the ashes of the burnt offering on the altar that had been consumed by the fire and set them beside the altar. 
03Lv 6:11 Then he is to change his clothes, dressing himself with a different set of clothes, and take the ashes to a clean place outside the camp.
03Lv 6:12 "The fire on the altar is to be kept burning continuously without being extinguished. The priest is to burn wood on it every morning, arrange burnt offerings over it, and then burn the fat contained in the peace offerings over it. 
03Lv 6:13 The fire is to continue to burn on the altar and is never to be extinguished."
03Lv 6:14 "This is the law concerning grain offerings. Aaron's sons are to offer it in the Lord's presence, in front of the altar. 
03Lv 6:15 He is to take a handful of fine flour for a grain offering, some olive oil, all of the frankincense on the grain offering, and make a sacrifice of smoke on the altar as a memorial portion, a pleasing aroma to the Lord.
03Lv 6:16 "Aaron and his sons are to eat what remains of the unleavened offering at this sacred place£º the court of the tent of meeting. 
03Lv 6:17 It is not to be baked with leaven. I've given it as their portion out of my offerings made by fire. It's a most holy thing, like the sin and guilt offerings. 
03Lv 6:18 Every male of Aaron's sons is to eat it as a portion continuously allotted for your generations from the offerings made by fire to the Lord. Anyone who touches them is to be holy."
03Lv 6:19 Then the Lord told Moses,
03Lv 6:20 "This is the offering that Aaron and his sons are to offer to the Lord the day he is anointed£º a tenth of an ephah of flour is to be offered throughout the day, half in the morning and half in the evening. 
03Lv 6:21 It is to be prepared with olive oil on a griddle. Once is has been mixed thoroughly, bake it, bring it in pieces, and offer it like a grain offering of broken pieces, a pleasing aroma to the Lord. 
03Lv 6:22 The anointed priest who succeeds him from among his sons is to offer it. As a permanent statute, it is to be offered whole and made to smoke in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 6:23 Every grain offering from a priest is to be burned whole. It is not to be eaten."
03Lv 6:24 Then the Lord told Moses, 
03Lv 6:25 "Speak to Aaron and his sons. This is the regulation concerning sin offerings. Slaughter the sin offering in the same place where the whole burnt offering is slaughtered - in the Lord's presence. It's a most holy thing. 
03Lv 6:26 The priest who offers it as a sin offering is to eat it at a sacred place in the court of the tent of meeting. 
03Lv 6:27 Whoever touches its meat will be holy. "If some of its blood spatters on a garment, wash where it was spattered in a sacred place. 
03Lv 6:28 The earthen vessel in which it was boiled is to be broken, unless it was boiled in a bronze vessel, in which case it is to be polished very well and rinsed in water.
03Lv 6:29 "Every male among the priests is to eat it. It's a most sacred thing. 
03Lv 6:30 Any sin offering from which its blood was brought to the tent of meeting to make atonement in the sacred place is not to be eaten. Instead, it is to be incinerated."
03Lv 7:1 "This is the regulation concerning guilt offerings. It's most holy. 
03Lv 7:2 The guilt offering is to be offered in the same place where the burnt offering is slaughtered. The priest is to spatter some of its blood on the altar and around it. 
03Lv 7:3 As to all its fat, that is, the fat on the tail and the fat covering the internal organs, the one presenting the sacrifice is to offer it. 
03Lv 7:4 But the two kidneys, the fat over them by the loins, and the appendage on the liver is to be taken away, along with the kidneys. 
03Lv 7:5 Then the priest is to offer them on the altar, incinerating them with fire as a guilt offering to the Lord. 
03Lv 7:6 Any male among the priests may eat it, provided that it is eaten at a sacred place as a most holy thing. 
03Lv 7:7 The law for the sin offering is the same as the guilt offering. It belongs to the priest who made atonement with it.
03Lv 7:8 "The hide from the burnt offering brought by the offeror is to belong to the priest.
03Lv 7:9 Every grain offering that's baked on the oven and every thing that's prepared on a stew pan or on the frying pan belongs to the priest who offered it. 
03Lv 7:10 Furthermore, every grain offering that's mixed with olive oil or that's dry will be for Aaron's sons, each one like the other. 
03Lv 7:11 "This is the law concerning the sacrifice for peace offerings that are to be brought to the Lord. 
03Lv 7:12 If someone brings it to demonstrate thanksgiving, then he is to present along with the thanksgiving offering unleavened cakes mixed with olive oil, unleavened wafers spread with olive oil, and cakes of mixed fine flour with olive oil. 
03Lv 7:13 Along with the cakes of unleavened bread, he is to bring his thanksgiving offering with his peace offerings. 
03Lv 7:14 He is to present one from each grain offering, a separate offering to the Lord. It will belong to the priest who spatters the blood of the peace offering. 
03Lv 7:15 As to the meat contained in his peace offerings, it is to be eaten on the day it is offered. Nothing of it is to remain until morning.13
03Lv 7:16 "If his sacrifice accompanies a fulfilled vow or is a voluntary offering, it is to be eaten on the day the offeror brings the sacrifice. Anything left over is to be eaten the next day, 
03Lv 7:17 but whatever remains uneaten from the meat of the sacrifice by the third day is to be incinerated.
03Lv 7:18 "If any of the meat of his sacrifice of peace offerings is eaten on the third day, it won't be accepted for the one who brought it. It is to be considered as refuse, and whoever eats it will bear the punishment of his iniquity. 
03Lv 7:19 "Meat that comes in contact with a ceremonially unclean thing is not to be eaten. Incinerate it instead. As for ceremonially clean meat, any one who is clean may eat it. 
03Lv 7:20 But the person who eats meat from the sacrifice that belongs to the Lord, while still affected by his uncleanness is to be eliminated from contact with his people. 
03Lv 7:21 Any person who touches a ceremonially unclean thing - whether the uncleanness pertains to human beings, animals, or to creeping things - and then eats from the meat of peace offerings that belongs to the Lord is to be eliminated from contact with his people."
03Lv 7:22 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 7:23 "Tell the Israelites£º You are not to eat the fat of an ox, a lamb, or a goat.
03Lv 7:24 "The carcass of an animal that died of its own and an animal torn by wild beast may be used for any purpose except for eating.
03Lv 7:25 "Anyone who eats the fat of an animal that has been offered by fire to the Lord is to be eliminated from contact with his people. 
03Lv 7:26 You are not to eat any form of blood in any of your dwellings, whether it's from birds or animals. 
03Lv 7:27 Any person who eats any form of blood is to be eliminated from contact with his people."
03Lv 7:28 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 7:29 Tell the Israelites£º "Whoever brings a peace offering sacrifice to the Lord is to bring his offering to the Lord from the sacrifice of his peace offerings. 
03Lv 7:30 He is to bring the offering made by fire with his own hands to the Lord. He is to bring the fat with the breast, since the breast is to be waved as a raised offering to the Lord. 
03Lv 7:31 The priest will burn the fat on the altar, but the breast belongs to Aaron and his sons. 
03Lv 7:32 From the sacrifices of your peace offerings give the right thigh to the priest as a raised offering to the Lord.
03Lv 7:33 "The descendant of Aaron's sons who brings the blood from the peace offering and the fat will have the right thigh for his own portion, 
03Lv 7:34 since I've taken the breast and the thigh as raised offerings from the sacrifices of peace offerings of the Israelites and have given them to Aaron the priest and his sons as their perpetual portion from the Israelites."
03Lv 7:35 This is the consecrated portion for Aaron and his descendants from the offerings made by fire to the Lord, the day they were presented to be priests to the Lord. 
03Lv 7:36 This is what the Lord had commanded to give them the day he anointed them from among the Israelites - a perpetual portion for their generations.
03Lv 7:37 This is the regulation concerning burnt, grain, sin, guilt, and installation offerings, along with the sacrifice for peace offerings. 
03Lv 7:38 This is what the Lord had commanded Moses on Mount Sinai on the day when he commanded the Israelites to bring their offerings to the Lord in the Sinai wilderness. 
03Lv 8:1 The Lord spoke to Moses£º 
03Lv 8:2 "Take Aaron, his sons with him, the clothing, the anointing oil, the bull for sin offering, two rams, and a basket of unleavened bread 
03Lv 8:3 and then assemble the entire congregation at the entrance of the tent of meeting.
03Lv 8:4 So Moses did just as the Lord had commanded him. He assembled the congregation at the entrance of the tent of meeting.
03Lv 8:5 Moses said to the congregation, "This is what the Lord commanded to be done."
03Lv 8:6 Moses brought Aaron and his sons and washed them with water. 
03Lv 8:7 Then he clothed Aaron with the tunic, girded him with the band for priests, clothed him with the robe, placed the ephod on him, girded him with the skillfully weaved band of the ephod, and bound it on him. 
03Lv 8:8 He set the breastplate on him and placed the urim and thumin on top of the breastplate. 
03Lv 8:9 Then he set the turban on his head, and on the turban at the front he set the golden plate, the sacred crown that the Lord had commanded.
03Lv 8:10 After this, Moses took the anointing oil and anointed the tabernacle, consecrating everything that was in it. 
03Lv 8:11 He spattered some on the altar seven times, then anointed the altar, all its vessels, the laver, and its base to consecrate them. 
03Lv 8:12 He then poured the oil of anointing on Aaron's head to anoint and consecrate him.
03Lv 8:13 Then Moses brought Aaron's sons, clothed them with the tunic, girded them with the bands, and bound turbans on them just as the Lord had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:14 Next, he brought the bull for sin offering. Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the bull's head for a sin offering. 
03Lv 8:15 So Moses slaughtered it, took the blood, and poured some of it at the horns of the altar and around it with his fingers, thus purifying the altar. Then he poured the blood at the base of the altar, thereby sanctifying it as a means to make atonement with it.
03Lv 8:16 Moses burned on the altar all the fat on the internal organs, the appendage on the liver, the two kidneys, and the fat. 
03Lv 8:17 As to the bull and its fat, skin and offal, he incinerated them outside the camp, just as the Lord had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:18 Next he brought the ram for whole burnt offering. Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram. 
03Lv 8:19 Moses slaughtered it and poured its blood over the altar and around it.
03Lv 8:20 As to the ram, he has cut it into parts at the joints. Moses burned the head, internal organs, and the fat.
03Lv 8:21 Moses washed the internal organs and the thigh with water and then burned the entire ram on the altar as a whole burnt offering, a pleasing aroma of an offering made by fire to the Lord, just as the Lord had commanded Moses.
03Lv 8:22 Moses brought the ram, that is, the second of the rams for consecration. Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram. 
03Lv 8:23 Moses then slaughtered it, took some of its blood, and put it on Aaron's right earlobe, right thumb, and on his right great toe. 
03Lv 8:24 Then Moses brought Aaron's sons, took some of its blood, and put it on their right earlobes, on their right thumbs, and on their right great toes. Moses poured the blood on the altar and all around it. 
03Lv 8:25 Then he took the fat - from the tail, all the fat on the internal organs, the appendage of the liver, the two kidneys with the fat, and the right thigh. 
03Lv 8:26 From the basket of unleavened bread, which is in the Lord's presence, he took one piece of unleavened bread, one cake spread with olive oil, and one wafer, which he placed over the fat and the right thigh.
03Lv 8:27 He put all of these things in the hands of Aaron and his sons, and they all waved them in a raised offering to the Lord. 
03Lv 8:28 After this, Moses took those things from their hands and burned them on the altar over the whole burnt offering for consecration. They served as a pleasing aroma, an offering made by fire to the Lord.
03Lv 8:29 Moses took the breast and waved it as a raised offering in the Lord's presence as the portion that belonged to Moses from the ram of consecration, just as the Lord had commanded Moses. 
03Lv 8:30 Moses took some anointing oil and blood that was on the altar and spattered it on Aaron, on his clothes, on his sons, and on their clothes, consecrating Aaron, his clothes, his sons, and their clothes. 
