03Lv 14:35 then the owner of the house is to approach the priest and tell him, 'There appears to be a contagion in the house.' 
03Lv 14:36 The priest is to command that the house be cleared before he comes to examine the contagion so that not everything in the house becomes unclean. "After this, the priest is to enter the house and examine it. 
03Lv 14:37 He is to determine if the contagion is indeed on the walls of the house, with greenish or reddish streaks and to determine if it appears to be deeper than the surface of the wall. 
03Lv 14:38 The priest is to leave through the entrance to the house and seal the house for seven days. 
03Lv 14:39 He is to return after seven days to examine it. If the contagion has spread to the walls of the house, 
03Lv 14:40 then the priest is to command that they take out the contaminated stones and discard them in an unclean place outside the city.
03Lv 14:41 "Now as for the house, they are to scrape off inside and outside the house and then discard the torn out plaster in an unclean place outside the city. 
03Lv 14:42 They are then to take other stones and bring them to replace those stones. Lastly, they are to replaster the house. 
03Lv 14:43 "If the contagion returns and spreads throughout the house after the stones have been removed, after the house has been scraped out, and after it had been re-coated, 
03Lv 14:44 and the priest comes, undertakes an examination, and determines that the contagion has spread in the house, it's a chronic fungal infection in the house. It's unclean.
03Lv 14:45 "He is to pull down the house, its stones, its lumber, and all the plaster on the house, and discard them in an unclean place outside the city. 
03Lv 14:46 Moreover, whoever enters the house during the time it was isolated is to be considered unclean until the evening. 
03Lv 14:47 Whoever slept in the house is to wash his clothes, along with whoever has eaten in the house.
03Lv 14:48 "But if the priest comes in to conduct an examination and determines that the contagion has not spread throughout the house after the house has been repaired, then the priest may declare the house clean, because the contagion has been cleansed.
03Lv 14:49 In order to cleanse the house, he is to take two birds, some cedar wood, two crimson threads, and some hyssop. 
03Lv 14:50 Then he is to slaughter one bird on an earthen vessel over flowing water. 
03Lv 14:51 He is to take the cedar wood, the hyssop, the two crimson threads, and the live bird, and dip them in the blood of the slaughtered bird over flowing water. Then he is to spatter the house seven times.
03Lv 14:52 "He is to clean the house with the blood of the bird over flowing water, including cleansing the live bird, the cedar wood, the hyssop, and the crimson thread. 
03Lv 14:53 Then he is to send the bird away, outside the city, facing the fields, to make atonement for the house. Then it is to be considered clean. 
03Lv 14:54 This is the law for every contagion of infectious skin disease and scabs, 
03Lv 14:55 for fungal infections on clothing or in a house, 
03Lv 14:56 for swelling of the skin, scabs, and bright spot, 
03Lv 14:57 to distinguish when it's unclean and clean. This is the law for infectious skin diseases."
03Lv 15:1 The Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron. 
03Lv 15:2 "Tell the Israelites that when a man has a discharge from his body, his discharge is unclean. 
03Lv 15:3 And this is the cause of his uncleaness - his discharge. Whether his body is releasing the discharge or his body has stopped the discharge, he's unclean. 
03Lv 15:4 Every bed on which he lies down with the discharge is to be considered unclean, and every object on which he sits becomes unclean.
03Lv 15:5 "Any person who touches his bed is to wash his garments and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:6 "Whoever sits on any object on which the one with the discharge had sat is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:7 "Whoever touches the body of someone with a discharge is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:8 "Whoever has a discharge and spits on someone who is clean, then he is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:9 "Any saddle that anyone with a discharge rides on will become unclean. 
03Lv 15:10 Whoever touches anything that was under him will be unclean until evening. Whoever carries them is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:11 "Anyone whom the one with the discharge touches without rinsing his hands with water is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening. 
03Lv 15:12 The earthen vessels that the person with the discharge touches is to be broken in pieces, and every wooden vessel is to be rinsed with water."
03Lv 15:13 "When the one with the discharge is cleansed from his discharge, then he is to set aside for himself seven days for his cleansing. He is to wash his clothes and bathe with flowing water. Then he will be clean.
03Lv 15:14 "On the eighth day, he is to take for himself two turtledoves or two young doves and bring them to the Lord at the entrance of the tent of meeting and give it to the priest. 
03Lv 15:15 Then the priest is to offer them, one for a sin offering and the other for a whole burnt offering. That's how the priest will make atonement for him in the Lord's presence regarding his discharge. 
03Lv 15:16 "If a man has a seminal emission, he is to bathe his entire body with water and remain unclean until evening. 
03Lv 15:17 Every garment, including leather, on which the semen is found is to be washed with water, and it will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:18 "When a man has sexual relations with a woman and the man releases semen, both are to bathe with water, and they will remain unclean until evening."
03Lv 15:19 "When a woman has a discharge and the blood is her monthly menstrual discharge from her body, then for seven days she'll remain in her menstrual uncleanness. Whoever touches her will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:20 "Everything that she sleeps on during her uncleanness will be unclean. Moreover, everything that she sits on will become unclean.
03Lv 15:21 "Anyone who touches her bed is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:22 "Anyone who touches any of the objects on which she has sat is to wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he will remain unclean until evening. 
03Lv 15:23 Any bed or other object on which she sat that he touches will make him unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:24 "When a man has sexual relations with her and her menstrual uncleanness touches him, he will be unclean for seven days. Every bed where he sleeps will remain unclean.
03Lv 15:25 "When a woman has a continuous discharge of blood many days beyond the time of her menstrual uncleanness, or if she has a discharge that lasts beyond the days of her menstrual uncleanness, her uncleanness is to be treated like the days of her menstruation£º she's unclean.
03Lv 15:26 "Every bed where she sleeps on the whole time she has the discharge will be her own unclean bed so that every object on which she sits becomes unclean like her menstrual uncleanness. 
03Lv 15:27 Whoever touches them will become unclean. He is to wash his clothes and bathe with water and he will remain unclean until evening.
03Lv 15:28 "If she becomes clean with her discharge, then she is to count for herself seven days after which she becomes clean. 
03Lv 15:29 On the eighth day, she is to take for herself two turtledoves or two young pigeons and bring them to the priest at the entrance of the tent of meeting. 
03Lv 15:30 Then the priest is to offer one for a sin offering and the other for a whole burnt offering. This is how the priest will make atonement in the Lord's presence for her regarding her unclean discharge. 
03Lv 15:31 "So separate the Israelites from their uncleanness so that they won't die in their uncleanness if they defile my tabernacle that is in their midst. 
03Lv 15:32 These are the regulations for one whose discharge of semen causes him to become unclean because of it, 
03Lv 15:33 and for her whose menstruation causes her to become ill, for anyone who has a discharge, whether male or female, and for the man who has sexual relations with one who is unclean."
03Lv 16:1 The Lord spoke to Moses after the death of Aaron's two sons when they had approached the Lord and died.
03Lv 16:2 The Lord said to Moses. "Remind your brother Aaron that at no time is he to enter the sacred place from the room that contains the curtain into the presence of the Mercy Seat on top of the ark. Otherwise, he'll die, because I will appear in a cloud at the Mercy Seat.
03Lv 16:3 "aron is to enter the sacred place with a young bull for a sin offering and a ram for a whole burnt offering. 
03Lv 16:4 He is to wear a sacred linen tunic and linen breeches that will cover his genitals. He is to clothe himself with a sash and wrap his head with a linen turban. Because they are sacred garments, he is to wash himself with water before putting them on."
03Lv 16:5 "He is to take two male goats for a sin offering and one ram for a whole burnt offering from the assembly of the Israelites. 
03Lv 16:6 Then Aaron is to bring the bull as a sin offering for himself and make atonement for himself and his household. 
03Lv 16:7 "Then he is to take the two male goats and present them in the Lord's presence at the entrance of the tent of meeting. 
03Lv 16:8 Aaron is to cast lots over the two male goats - one lot for the Lord and the other one for the scapegoat.
03Lv 16:9 "Aaron then is to bring the male goat on which the lot fell for the Lord and offer it as a sin offering. 
03Lv 16:10 The male goat on which the lot fell for the scapegoat is to be brought alive into the Lord's presence to make atonement for himself. Then he is to send it into the wilderness."
03Lv 16:11 "Aaron is then to bring the bull for a sin offering for him, thus making atonement for himself and his household. He is to slaughter the ox for himself. 
03Lv 16:12 Then he is to take a censer, fill it with coals from the fire on the altar in the Lord's presence. With his hands full of spiced and refined incense, he is to bring it beyond the curtain.11
03Lv 16:13 "Then he is to place the incense over the fire in the Lord's presence, ensuring that the smoke from the incense covers the atonement place, according to regulation, so he won't die. 
03Lv 16:14 He is to take blood from the ox and spatter it with his forefinger toward the surface of the atonement place. Then he is to spatter the blood on the surface of the atonement place with his forefinger seven times.
03Lv 16:15 "He is to slaughter the male goat as a sin offering for the people and bring its blood beyond the curtain and do with its blood as he did with the blood of the bull£º He is to spatter it on the atonement place over the surface of the atonement place. 
03Lv 16:16 Then he is to make atonement on the sacred place on account of the uncleanness of the Israelites, their transgressions, and all their sins. This is how he is to act in the tent of meeting, which will remain with them in the middle of their uncleanness.
03Lv 16:17 "No person is to be there when he enters the tent of meeting to make atonement in the sacred place until he comes out and has made atonement on account of himself, his household, and the entire assembly of Israel. 
03Lv 16:18 When he goes to the altar in the Lord's presence to make atonement for himself, then he is to take some of the blood from the bull and the male goat, place it around the horns of the altar, 
03Lv 16:19 spattering it with the blood on his forefinger seven times, cleansing and sanctifying it from Israel's sins."
03Lv 16:20 "When he has completed making atonement at the sacred place, the tent of meeting, and the altar, then he is to present the live male goat.
03Lv 16:21 Aaron is to lay his two hands upon the head of the male goat and confess over it the sins of Israel, all their transgressions, and all their sins, thus placing them on the head of the male goat that he'll then send out to the wilderness by the hand of a man capable of carrying out this task.  
03Lv 16:22 The male goat will bear on itself all their sins to a solitary land, as Aaron sends the goat out to the wilderness.
03Lv 16:23 "Then Aaron is to enter the tent of meeting, taking off his white linen clothes that he had put on when he entered the sacred place and leaving them there. 
03Lv 16:24 He is to wash his body with water at the sacred place and put on his clothes. Then he is to go out, offer a whole burnt offering for himself and a whole burnt offering for the people, thereby making atonement on account of himself and on account of the people.
03Lv 16:25 "As to the fat from the burnt offering, he is to incinerate it on the altar. 
03Lv 16:26 The one who sent away the male goat as a scapegoat is to wash his clothes and bathe his body with water. After doing so, he may enter the camp.
03Lv 16:27 "The bull for the sin offering and the male goat for the sin offering, whose blood was brought in to the sacred place, is to be taken outside the camp. Their skin, meat, and offal are to be incinerated. 
03Lv 16:28 The one who burns them is to wash his clothes and bathe his body with water. After doing so, he may enter the camp."
03Lv 16:29 "This is to be a perpetual statute for you. On the tenth day of the seventh month, you (including both the native born and the resident alien) are to humble yourselves by not doing any work, 
03Lv 16:30 because on that day, atonement will be made for you to cleanse you from all your sins. You are to be clean in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 16:31 It's the Sabbath of all Sabbaths for you, so humble yourselves. This is to be a perpetual statute. 
03Lv 16:32 "The priest who has been anointed and consecrated to be priest after his father is to make the atonement. He is to put on the sacred linen clothings 
03Lv 16:33 and make atonement for the sacred sanctuary, the tent of meeting, and the altar where atonement is carried out. He is also to make atonement for the priests and the people of the entire assembly. 
03Lv 16:34 This will be a perpetual statute for you as you make atonement once a year for the Israelites on account of all their sins." So Moses did just as the Lord had commanded him.
03Lv 17:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 17:2 "Speak to Aaron, his sons, and all the Israelites and tell them that this is what the Lord has commanded. 
03Lv 17:3 When a person from the house of Israel slaughters an ox, a lamb, or a goat, whether in the camp or outside the camp, 
03Lv 17:4 but fails to bring it to the entrance of the tent of meeting as an offering in the presence of the tabernacle of the Lord, that person will incur blood guiltiness. Because he has shed blood, that person is to be eliminated from  contact with his people."
03Lv 17:5 "This statute is required so that the Israelites may bring their sacrifices that they are sacrificing in the open field to the Lord, to the priest at the entrance of the tent of meeting, where they are to slaughter their peace offering to the Lord. 
03Lv 17:6 The priest is to spatter the blood on the Lord's altar at the entrance of the tent of meeting and incinerate the fat, making a pleasing aroma to the Lord. 
03Lv 17:7 They are no longer to slaughter their sacrifices to the goat demons, with whom they have committed prostitution. This will be a perpetual statute for you throughout your generations."17
03Lv 17:8 "Tell them that if a person from the house of Israel or a resident alien who lives among you brings a whole burnt offering or a sacrifice 
03Lv 17:9 to the entrance of the tent of meeting, but fails to bring it to offer it to the Lord, that person is to be eliminated from  contact with his people."
03Lv 17:10 "If anyone from the house of Israel or a resident alien who lives among them eats any form of blood, I'll oppose that person who ate the blood and eliminate him from his people, 
03Lv 17:11 because the life of the flesh is in the blood itself, and I myself have given it to you all so that atonement may be made for your souls on the altar, since the blood itself makes atonement through the life that is in it. 
03Lv 17:12 This is why I've said to the Israelites that no person among you is to eat blood. Even the resident alien who lives among you is not to eat blood.
03Lv 17:13 "If a person from the house of Israel or a resident alien who lives among you has hunted live game or a bird that may be eaten, he is to extract its blood and cover it with soil, 
03Lv 17:14 because the life of any flesh is the blood itself. Therefore I'm saying to the Israelites that the blood of any flesh is not to be eaten, because the life of any flesh is in its blood. Anyone who eats of it is to be eliminated from  contact with his people. 
03Lv 17:15 "Any person who eats a carcass or an animal that was torn by beasts, whether that person is native born or a resident alien, is to wash his clothes and bathe himself with water, and he will remain unclean until evening, and then he'll become clean. 
03Lv 17:16 But if he doesn't wash or bathe his body, then he is to bear the punishment of his iniquity."
03Lv 18:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 18:2 Tell the Israelites that I am the Lord your God. 
03Lv 18:3 You are not to do what you used to do in the land Egypt where you lived. You are not to do what Canaan does, where I'm about to bring you, so that you live according to their statutes. 
03Lv 18:4 Obey my ordinances and keep my statutes by living by them. I am the Lord your God.
03Lv 18:5 "Keep my statutes and my ordinances, which a person is to obey in order to live in them. I am the Lord.
03Lv 18:6 "A person is not to approach a near blood relative for sexual relations. I am the Lord.
03Lv 18:7 "Neither your father's nakedness nor your mother's nakedness is to be exposed. She's your mother, you are not to have sexual relations with her.
03Lv 18:8 "You are not to have sexual relations with your father's wife. It's your own father's nakedness.
03Lv 18:9 "You are not to have sexual relations with your sister, whether she's your father's daughter or your mother's daughter, whether she's born in your home or outside your home. You are not to have sexual relations with them.
03Lv 18:10 "You are not to have sexual relations with your son's daughter or your daughter's daughter. You are not to have sexual relations with them, because their nakedness is your own nakedness.
03Lv 18:11 "You are not to have sexual relations with the daughter of your father's wife. Born of your father, she's your sister, so you are not to have sexual relations with her.
03Lv 18:12 "You are not to have sexual relations with your father's sister. She's your father's near blood relative.
03Lv 18:13 "You are not to have sexual relations with your mother's sister. She's your mother's near blood relative.
03Lv 18:14 "You are not to expose the nakedness of your father's brother by having sexual relations with his wife. She's your aunt.
03Lv 18:15 "You are not to expose the nakedness of your daughter-in-law. She's the wife of your son. You are not to have sexual relations with her.
03Lv 18:16 "You are not to have sexual relations with your brother's wife. She's the nakedness of your brother.
03Lv 18:17 "You are not to have sexual relations with a woman and her daughter. "You are not to have sexual relations with her son's daughter or her daughter's daughter. They're near blood relatives. It's wickedness.
03Lv 18:18 "You are not to marry a woman and then have sexual relations with her sister as a rival when your wife is still alive.
03Lv 18:19 "You are not to approach a menstruating woman to have sexual relations with her.
03Lv 18:20 "You are not to have sexual relations with your neighbor's wife and thereby become ceremonially unclean with her."
03Lv 18:21 "You are not to present any of your children to Molech as a sacrifice. That way, you won't defile the name of your God." "I am the Lord. 
03Lv 18:22 You are not to have sexual relations with a male as you would with a woman. It's detestable."
03Lv 18:23 "You are not to present yourself to an animal in order to have sexual relations with it and by doing so to defile yourself. Even a woman is not to present herself to an animal to have sexual relations with it. It's detestable.18
03Lv 18:24 "You are not to defile yourselves by doing any of these things, since all of these nations that I'm casting out before you have defiled themselves this way. 
03Lv 18:25 The land has been defiled, so I brought the punishment of its iniquity to it. As a result, the land is vomiting out its inhabitants.
03Lv 18:26 "Therefore, keep my statutes and ordinances. You are not to do any of these detestable things - this applies to the native born and the resident alien who lives among you -  
03Lv 18:27 because the inhabitants of the land did all of these detestable things and by doing so defiled the land before you. 
03Lv 18:28 So you are not to let the land vomit you up because of your uncleanness as it is vomiting the nations that were here before you. 
03Lv 18:29 Anyone who does any of these detestable things - whoever the person may be - is to be eliminated from contact with his people. 
03Lv 18:30 Therefore keep my injunctions so that you won't practice these detestable things that have been done before you, and so that you won't be defiled in them. I am the Lord."
03Lv 19:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 19:2 "Tell the entire assembly of Israel that they are to be holy, since I, the Lord your God, am holy.
03Lv 19:3 "Each of you is to fear his mother and father. "Observe my Sabbaths. I am the Lord your God.
03Lv 19:4 "You are not to turn to their idols or cast gods out of melted metal for yourselves. I am the Lord you God.
03Lv 19:5 "When you offer peace offerings to the Lord, offer it for your acceptance. 
03Lv 19:6 Your sacrifice is to be eaten on that day and the next day. Any that remains to the third day is to be incinerated. 
03Lv 19:7 Since it's eaten on the third day, it's unclean. It won't be accepted. 
03Lv 19:8 Any one who eats it will bear the punishment of his sin, since he will have defiled himself regarding the Lord's holy things. That person is to be eliminated from  contact with his people."
03Lv 19:9 "When you reap the harvest of your land, you are not to completely finish harvesting the corners of the field, that is, you are not to pick what remains after you have reaped your harvest. 
03Lv 19:10 You are not to gather your vineyard or pick up the fallen grapes of your vineyard. Leave something for the poor and the resident alien who lives among you. I am the Lord your God."
03Lv 19:11 "You are not to steal or lie or deal falsely with your neighbor.
03Lv 19:12 "You are not to use my name to deceive, thereby defiling the name of your God. I am the Lord.
03Lv 19:13 "You are not to oppress your neighbor or rob him. "The wages of a hired labourer are not to remain in your possession until morning.
03Lv 19:14 "You are not to curse a deaf person or put a stumbling block before the blind. "You are to fear God. I am the Lord."
03Lv 19:15 "You are not to be unjust in deciding a case. You are not to show partiality to the poor or honor the great. Instead, decide the case of your neighbor with righteousness."
03Lv 19:16 "You are not to go around slandering your people. "You are not to stand idle  when your neighbor's life is at stake. I am the Lord.
03Lv 19:17 "You are not to hate your relative in your heart. Rebuke your neighbor if you must, but you are not to incur guilt on account of him.
03Lv 19:18 "You are not to seek vengeance or hold a grudge against the descendants of your people. Instead, love your neighbor as yourself. I am the Lord."
03Lv 19:19 "Observe my statutes. "You are not to let your cattle breed with a different species. "You are not to sow your fields with two different kinds of seeds. "You are not to wear clothing made from two different kinds of material.
03Lv 19:20 "When a person has sexual relations with a woman servant  who is engaged to another man, but she had not been completely redeemed nor had her freedom been granted to her, there is to be an inquiry, but they won't be put to death, since she had not been freed.
03Lv 19:21 "The perpetrator is to bring his guilt offering to the Lord at the entrance of the tent of meeting, along with a ram as guilt offering. 
03Lv 19:22 Then the priest is to make atonement for him with the ram as guilt offering in the Lord's presence on account of his sin which he had committed but which has been forgiven him." 
03Lv 19:23 "When you have entered the land and planted all sorts of trees for food, regard its fruit as uncircumcised for the first three years for you. It is not to be eaten.
03Lv 19:24 During the fourth year, all its fruit is to offered as a holy token of praise to the Lord. 
03Lv 19:25 But on the fifth year, you may eat its fruits to increase its produce for you."
03Lv 19:26 "You are not to eat anything containing blood, engage in occult practices, or practice fortune telling.19
03Lv 19:27 "You are not to cut your hair in ritualistic patterns on your heads or deface the edges of your beard.
03Lv 19:28 "You are not to make incisions in your flesh on account of the dead nor submit to cuts or tattoos. I am the Lord.
03Lv 19:29 "You are not to defile your daughter by engaging her in prostitution so the land won't become  filled with wickedness. 
03Lv 19:30 "Observe my Sabbath and stand in awe of my sanctuary. I am the Lord.
03Lv 19:31 "You are to consult neither mediums nor familiar spirits.  You are never to seek them - you'll just be defiled by them. I am the Lord your God.
03Lv 19:32 "Rise in the presence of the aged and honor the elderly face-to-face. "Fear your God. I am the Lord. 
03Lv 19:33 "If a resident alien lives with you in your land, you are not to mistreat him. 
03Lv 19:34 You are to treat the resident alien the same way you treat the native born among you - love him like yourself, since you were foreigners in the land of Egypt.
03Lv 19:35 "You are not to act unjustly in deciding a case or when measuring weight and quantity. 
03Lv 19:36 You are to maintain just balances and reliable standards for weights, dry volumes, and liquid volumes. I am the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt. 
03Lv 19:37 Observe all my statutes and all my ordinances in order to practice them. I am the Lord."
03Lv 20:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
