03Lv 21:1 The Lord told Moses, "Speak to the priests, Aaron's sons, and tell them that no priest is to defile himself on account of the dead among his people, 
03Lv 21:2 except his close relatives - his mother or father, his son or daughter, or his brother or 
03Lv 21:3 his virgin sister who is near him who doesn't have a husband, he may defile himself for her.
03Lv 21:4 "Because he is a husband among his people, he is not to defile himself, thereby polluting himself.
03Lv 21:5 "They are not to cut their hair in ritualistic patterns on their heads or deface the edges of their beards, or make incisions in their flesh. 
03Lv 21:6 They are to be holy to their God. They are not to defile the name of their God, because they're the ones who bring the offerings of the Lord made by fire - the food of their God - so they are to be holy. 
03Lv 21:7 "They are not to marry a prostitute, a woman who has been dishonored, or who was divorced from her husband, because the priest is holy to his God. 
03Lv 21:8 Consecrate him, because he's the one who offers the food of your God. He is to be holy for you, because I the Lord - the one who sanctifies you - am holy.
03Lv 21:9 "Now if the daughter of any priest defiles herself by being a prostitute, she defiles her father. She is to be incinerated.
03Lv 21:1 0"The high priest among his relatives, whose head has been anointed with oil and who has been consecrated to put on the priestly clothings, is not to let his hair hang loose or to tear his clothes. 
03Lv 21:1 1He is not to come near any dead body, whether the deceased is his father or his mother, so as not to defile himself. 
03Lv 21:1 2He is not to go out of the sanctuary or defile the sanctuary of his God, because his God's consecrating oil of anointing rests on him. I am the Lord.
03Lv 21:1 3"Furthermore, he is to marry a true virgin. 
03Lv 21:1 4He is not to marry a widow, one who has been divorced, has been defiled, or who has been a prostitute. Instead, he is to take a virgin from among his people as his wife.
03Lv 21:1 5"He is not to defile his children among his people, because I am the Lord, who sets him apart."
03Lv 21:1 6The Lord told Moses, 
03Lv 21:1 7"Tell Aaron that whoever of your descendants throughout their generations has a bodily defect is not to approach to offer the food of his God. 
03Lv 21:18 Indeed, any person who has a defect is not to approach the tent of meeting£º the blind, the lame, one who is mutilated in the face, or who has a very long limb, 
03Lv 21:19 a person who has a fractured foot or hand, 
03Lv 21:20 a haunched back, a dwarf, or one with an eye defect, an itching disease, scabs or a crushed testicle.
