03Lv 22:1 Later on, the Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 22:2 "Tell Aaron and his sons that they are to separate themselves for the sacred things of the Israelites and that they are not to defile my holy name. I am the Lord.
03Lv 22:3 "Tell them that whoever among your descendants throughout your generations approaches the sacred things that the Israelites had consecrated to the Lord while still remaining unclean is to be eliminated from my presence. I am the Lord.
03Lv 22:4 "If one of Aaron's descendants has an infectious skin disease or a discharge, he is not to eat anything sacred until he has been cleansed. Anyone who touches an unclean thing on account of the dead, or who has a seminal discharge, 
03Lv 22:5 or who becomes unclean by touching a creeping creature or another human being whatever the uncleanness may be.
03Lv 22:6 "The person who comes in contact with anything like this will become unclean until evening. As a result, he is not to eat the sacred things unless he has bathed himself with water.
03Lv 22:7 When the sun has gone down and he has been cleansed, he may eat of the sacred things, since that's his food.
03Lv 22:8 "He is not to eat a carcass and an animal that was torn by animals, thereby defiling himself with it. I am the Lord.
03Lv 22:9 "They are to keep my charge. By doing so, they won't bear the punishment of sin because of it and therefore die if they've been defiled by it. I am the Lord who sets them apart."
03Lv 22:10 "No resident alien is to eat anything sacred. Neither the visitor of the priest nor a hired laborer is to eat anything sacred. 
03Lv 22:11 If a priest acquires a slave as property with his own money, he may eat with him. Those who were born in his house may eat his food.
03Lv 22:12 "If a priest's daughter marries a resident alien, she is not to eat the sacred raised offerings. 
03Lv 22:13 If the priest's daughter is a widow, or is divorced and childless, so that she has to return to her father's house as in her younger days, she may eat her father's food, but no resident alien may eat it.
03Lv 22:14 "If a person eats anything sacred inadvertently; he is to add a fifth part to it and then give the sacred thing to the priest.
03Lv 22:15 "Because I am the Lord who sets them apart, they are not to defile the sacred things of the Israelites that they have offered to the Lord, thereby causing them to bear the punishment of their iniquity for wrong doing, when they eat their sacred things."
03Lv 22:17 The Lord spoke to Moses,
03Lv 22:18 "Tell Aaron, his sons, and all the Israelites that when a person from the house of Israel or from the resident aliens living in Israel brings his offering to the Lord as a whole burnt offering (whether votive or free will offerings), 
03Lv 22:19 so that you'll be sure to be accepted, he is to offer a male without defect from the bulls, the lamb, and the goats.
03Lv 22:20 "However, whatever has a defect is not to be offered, because it won't be acceptable for you.
03Lv 22:21 "If a person brings a peace offering sacrifice to the Lord to fulfill a vow or a free will offering from the herd or the flock, it is to be sound in order to be accepted, without any defect in it.
03Lv 22:22 "You are not to bring an offering that is blind, fractured, mutilated, or infected with ulcers, scurvy, or scales to the Lord. You are not to present as an offering made by fire any of them on the altar for the Lord.
03Lv 22:23 "You may offer a bull or lamb that has one limb longer than the other or that is stunted as a free will offering, but it's not acceptable as a votive offering. 
03Lv 22:24 You are not to bring an animal that has been emasculated, crushed, torn, or cut apart to the Lord. You are not to practice this in your land. 
03Lv 22:25 A resident alien is not to offer as food to your God any of these items, because they are afflicted with ritual corruption due to their defects. They're not acceptable for you."
03Lv 22:26 The Lord told Moses, 
03Lv 22:27 "Whenever a bull, a sheep, or a goat is born, it is to remain for seven days under the care of its mother. But on the eighth day onwards, it may be accepted as an offering made by fire to the Lord. 
03Lv 22:28 However, you are not to slaughter a bull or a ewe along with its offspring on the same day. 
03Lv 22:29 When you offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving to the Lord, bring it so that it's acceptable for you. 
03Lv 22:30 It is to be eaten that same day. You are not to leave any of it until morning. I am the Lord.
03Lv 22:31 "Keep my commands and observe them. I am the Lord.
03Lv 22:32 "You are not to defile my sacred name, because I've been set apart in the midst of the Israelites. Furthermore, I am the Lord who sets you apart, 
03Lv 22:33 who brought you out of the land of Egypt to be your God. I am the Lord."
03Lv 23:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 23:2 Tell the Israelites, "These are my feast times appointed by the Lord that  you are to declare as sacred assemblies.
03Lv 23:3 Six days you may work, but the seventh day is a Sabbath of rest, a sacred assembly. You are not to do any work. It's a Sabbath to the Lord wherever you live. 
03Lv 23:4 These are the Lord's appointed feasts, sacred assemblies that you are to declare at their appointed time.3
03Lv 23:5 "The Lord's Passover is to begin on the fourteenth day of the first month at twilight. 
03Lv 23:6 "On the fifteenth day of that month is the Feast of Unleavened Bread to the Lord. For seven days you are to eat unleavened bread. 
03Lv 23:7 On the first day that you hold the sacred assembly you are to do no servile work. 
03Lv 23:8 Instead, you are to bring an offering made by fire to the Lord daily for seven days. On the seventh day you are also to hold a sacred assembly during which you are to do no servile work."
03Lv 23:9 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 23:10 "Tell the Israelites that when you enter the land that I'm about to give you and gather its produce, you are to bring a sheaf from the first portion of your harvest to the priest, 
03Lv 23:11 who will offer the sheaf in the Lord's presence for your acceptance. The priest is to wave it on the day after the Sabbath.
03Lv 23:12 "On the day you wave the sheaf, you are to offer a one year old male lamb without defect for a burnt offering in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 23:13 Also present a meal offering of two tenths of a measure of fine flour mixed with olive oil as an offering made by fire to the Lord, a pleasing aroma. "Now as to a drink offering, you are to present a fourth of a hin of wine. 
03Lv 23:14 You are not to eat bread, parched grain, or fresh grain until that day when you've brought the offering of your God. This is to be an eternal ordinance throughout your generations, wherever you live."
03Lv 23:15 "Starting the day after the Sabbath, count for yourselves seven weeks from the day you brought the sheaf of wave offering. They are to be complete. 
03Lv 23:16 Count fifty days to the day after the seventh Sabbath, then bring a new meal offering to the Lord.
03Lv 23:17 "Bring two loaves of bread from home as wave offerings made from two tenths of fine flour, baked with leaven, as first fruits to the Lord.
03Lv 23:18 "Along with the loaves of bread, bring seven lambs, a year old without defect, one young bull as an offering, and two rams as offering to the Lord, along with your gift and drink offerings, and present them as an offering made by fire, a pleasing aroma to the Lord.
03Lv 23:19 "Prepare one male goat for a sin offering and two one year old rams for peace offerings. 
03Lv 23:20 Then the priest is to wave them - the two lambs with the bread of first fruits - as raised offering in the Lord's presence. They'll be sacred to the Lord on account of the priest.
03Lv 23:21 "On the same day proclaim a sacred assembly for yourselves. You are not to do any servile work - and this is to be an eternal ordinance wherever you live throughout your generations. 
03Lv 23:22 Furthermore, when you harvest the produce of your land, you are not to harvest all the way to the corners of your field or gather the gleanings of your harvest. Leave them for the poor and resident alien. I am the Lord your God.
03Lv 23:23 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 23:24 Tell the Israelites that on the first day of the seventh month you are to have a Sabbath of rest for you, a memorial announced by a loud blast of trumpets. It is to be a sacred assembly. 
03Lv 23:25 You are not to do any servile work. Instead bring an offering made by fire to the Lord. 
03Lv 23:26 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 23:27 "However, on the tenth day of this seventh month is the Day of Atonement. It's a sacred assembly for you. Humble yourselves and bring an offering made by fire to the Lord.
03Lv 23:28 "You are not to do any work that same day. It's the Day of Atonement, because your atonement is made in the presence of the Lord your God. 
03Lv 23:29 Anyone who doesn't humble himself that same day is to be eliminated from contact with his people. 
03Lv 23:30 I'll eliminate anyone who does work that day from among his people.
03Lv 23:31 You are not to do any work. This is to be an eternal ordinance throughout your generations wherever you live. 
03Lv 23:32 It's a Sabbath of rest for you, on which you are to humble yourselves starting the evening of the ninth day of the month. You are to observe your Sabbath from evening to evening."
03Lv 23:33 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 23:34 Tell the Israelites that starting the fifteenth day of this seventh month is the week-long Feast of Tabernacles to the Lord. 
03Lv 23:35 On the first day you are to hold a sacred assembly when you are not to do any servile work. 
03Lv 23:36 For seven days, bring offerings made by fire to the Lord. "The eighth day is also to be a sacred assembly for you. Bring offerings made by fire to the Lord. It's a sacred assembly. You are not to do any servile work.
03Lv 23:37 "These are the Lord's appointed feasts that you are to proclaim as sacred assemblies. Bring offerings made by fire to the Lord - a whole burnt offering, a meal offering, a sacrifice, and drink offerings. Do this every day on its assigned date 
03Lv 23:38 in addition to the Lord's Sabbath, regarding your gifts, and your offerings in fulfillment of vows, and your freely given offerings that you will bring to the Lord.23
03Lv 23:39 "On the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when you've harvested the produce of the land, you are to observe the feast of the Lord for seven days. The first day is  to be a Sabbath rest, and the eighth day also is to be a Sabbath rest.
03Lv 23:40 "On the first day, take branches from impressive fruit trees, branches from palm-trees, boughs from thick trees, and poplars from the brooks. Then you are to rejoice in the presence of the Lord your God for seven days. 
03Lv 23:41 Observe it as a pilgrimage feast in the presence of the Lord for seven days in the year. This is to be an eternal ordinance throughout your generations. Observe the feast during the seventh month. 
03Lv 23:42 You are to live in booths for seven days. Every native born of Israel is to live in booths 
03Lv 23:43 in order for your future generations to know that the Israelites lived in booths when I brought them out of the land of Egypt. I am the Lord your God."
03Lv 23:44 This is what Moses spoke about to the Israelites regarding the Lord's appointed feasts.
03Lv 24:1 The Lord spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 24:2 "Tell the Israelites that they are to bring to you pure oil made from beaten olives in order to keep the lamp burning continuously. 
03Lv 24:3 Outside the canopy of the testimony in the tent of meeting, Aaron is to arrange it continuously in the Lord's presence from evening until morning as an eternal ordinance throughout your generations. 
03Lv 24:4 He is to arrange the lamps so that they burn continuously on a ceremonially pure lampstand in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 24:5 "Take fine flour and bake twelve cakes using two tenths of a measure of for each cake. 
03Lv 24:6 Arrange them in two rows, six on each row on a ceremonially pure table in the Lord's presence. 
03Lv 24:7 Put pure frankincense on each row for a memorial offering. It will serve as an offering made by fire to the Lord. 
03Lv 24:8 Every Sabbath day they are to be arranged in the Lord's presence, as a gift from the Israelites, an eternal covenant. 
03Lv 24:9 This gift will belong to Aaron and his sons, and they are to eat it in a sacred place, because it's the most holy thing for him of all the offerings made by fire to the Lord. This is to be an eternal ordinance. 
03Lv 24:10 Now a son of an Israelite woman and an Egyptian man went out among the Israelites. The Israelite woman's son got into a fight with an Israelite man in the camp. 
03Lv 24:11 Then the Israelite woman's son blasphemed the Name and cursed, so they brought him to Moses. His mother's name was Shelomith, the daughter of Dibri, from the clan of Dan. 
03Lv 24:12 They placed him in custody until a decision would be made to them according to the word of the Lord. 
03Lv 24:13 The Lord then spoke to Moses, 
03Lv 24:14 "Take the one who cursed outside the camp. Everyone who had heard him is to lay their hands on his head. Then the entire congregation is to stone him to death. 
03Lv 24:15 Moreover, tell the Israelites that anyone who curses his God will bear the consequences of his own sin, because the one who blasphemes the name of the Lord is certainly to be put to death. The entire congregation is to stone him to death. 
03Lv 24:16 As it is for the resident alien so it is to be with the native born£º when he blasphemes the Name, he is to be put to death.
03Lv 24:17 "If a man beats a human being to death, he is certainly to be executed, 
03Lv 24:18 but whoever beats an animal to death is to replace it, life for life.
03Lv 24:19 "If a man disfigures his fellow, whatever he did is to be done to him also. 
03Lv 24:20 Fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, just as he had caused a disfigurement against another man, so it is to be done against him.
03Lv 24:21 "Whoever beats an animal to death is to replace it, but whoever who beats a human being to death is to be put to death.
03Lv 24:22 You are to have for yourselves consistent procedures in deciding a case. As it is for the resident alien, so it is for the native born. I am the Lord your God."
03Lv 24:23 So Moses spoke to the Israelites and they brought the one who cursed outside the camp and stoned him to death with boulders. The Israelites did just as the Lord had commanded Moses.
03Lv 25:1 The Lord spoke to Moses on Mount Sinai. 
03Lv 25:2 "Tell the Israelites that when you enter the land that I'm about to give you, you are to let the land observe a Sabbath to the Lord. 
03Lv 25:3 For six years you may plant your fields, and for six years you may prune your vineyard and gather its produce.
03Lv 25:4 "But the seventh year is to be a Sabbath of rest for the land - a Sabbath for the Lord. You are not to plant your field or prune your vineyard. 
03Lv 25:5 You are not to gather what grows from the spilled kernels of your crops. You are not to pick the grapes of your untrimmed vines. Let it be a year of Sabbath for the land. 
03Lv 25:6 You may take the Sabbath produce of the land for your food - you, your male and maid servants, your hired laborers, and the resident alien with you. 
03Lv 25:7 The cattle and the wild animals in your land - everything it produces - are for your food.4
03Lv 25:8 "Count for yourselves seven years of Sabbaths, seven times seven years. This set of seven weeks of years total forty nine years for you. 
03Lv 25:9 Sound a horn on the tenth day of the seventh month of this fiftieth year. Likewise on the Day of Atonement sound the horn throughout your land.
03Lv 25:10 "Set aside and consecrate the fiftieth year to declare liberty throughout the land for all of its inhabitants. It is to be a jubilee for you. Every person is to return to his own land that he has inherited. "Likewise, every person is to return to his clan. 
03Lv 25:11 The fiftieth year is to be a year of jubilee for you. You are not to sow or harvest the spilled kernels that grow of itself or pick grapes from the untrimmed vines 
03Lv 25:12 because it's jubilee. It's sacred for you. But you may eat its produce from the field.
03Lv 25:13 "During this year of jubilee, each person is to return to his own land that he has inherited. 
03Lv 25:14 So if you had sold property to a neighbor or had acquired land from your neighbor, you are not to cheat one another. 
03Lv 25:15 According to the number of years after the jubilee, you may buy from your neighbor. And according to the number of years with crops, he may sell to you. 
03Lv 25:16 If the number of years are more, increase the selling price. If the years be few, decrease its selling price, because he's selling to you according to the volume of produce. 
03Lv 25:17 No one is to cheat his neighbor. Instead, you are to fear your God, because I'm the Lord your God.
03Lv 25:18 "Observe my statutes and keep my ordinances. Do them so that you may live securely in the land. 
03Lv 25:19 Then the land will yield its fruit and you'll eat to your satisfaction and live securely.
03Lv 25:20 "Now if you ask, 'What will we eat during the seventh year -  After all, we may not plant or even gather our produce!' 
03Lv 25:21 I'll command my blessing on you during the sixth year so that it will yield produce for three years! 
03Lv 25:22 That way, you are to sow in the eighth year, eating the produce from the old harvest. Until the ninth year when its produce comes in, you'll eat from the old harvest."
03Lv 25:23 "The land is not to be sold with any finality, because the land belongs to me. You're sojourners and travelers with me. 
03Lv 25:24 So throughout all of your land inheritance, grant the right of redemption for the land. 
03Lv 25:25 "If your brother is poor so that he had to a sell portion of his inheritance, then his nearest kinsman redeemer is to come and redeem what his brother has sold. 
03Lv 25:26 If a person doesn't have a kinsman redeemer but has become rich and found sufficient means for his redemption, 
03Lv 25:27 then let him account for the years for which it was sold, return the excess to the person to whom it was sold, and then return to his property. 
03Lv 25:28 If he's not able to redeem it back for himself, then what he sold is to remain in the hand of the buyer until the year of jubilee. In the jubilee, it is to be returned so he may return to his property. 
03Lv 25:29 "If a person sells a residential house in a walled city, then he is to redeem it within the year in which it was sold. He may have right to its redemption for a full year. 
03Lv 25:30 But if it's not redeemed by the end of a full year, then the house next to which is a wall is to belong to the one who bought it, in perpetuity throughout his generations. It is not to be returned in the jubilee.
03Lv 25:31 "However, the houses in the villages that don't have walls around them are to be categorized along with the fields of the land. It may be redeemed, so it is to be returned in the jubilee.
03Lv 25:32 "Nevertheless, the cities that belong to the Levites - that is, the houses in the cities that belong to them - are to belong to the Levites perpetually as part of their right of redemption. 
03Lv 25:33 If someone from the Levites redeems the houses in the cities that they own, they are to be returned in the jubilee, because the houses of the cities of the Levites are to remain their property among the Israelites. 
03Lv 25:34 Also, the open land of their cities is not to be sold, because it is to remain their perpetual inheritance."
03Lv 25:35 If your relative becomes poor so that he is indebted to you, then you are to support him. You are to let him live with you just like the resident alien and the traveler. 
03Lv 25:36 You are not to take interest or profit from him. Instead, you are to fear your God and let your relative live with you.
03Lv 25:37 "You are not to loan him money with interest or sell him your food at a profit. 
03Lv 25:38 I'm the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to give you the land of Canaan, and to be your God. 
03Lv 25:39 "If your brother with you becomes poor, so that he sells himself to you, you are not to make him serve like a bond slave. 
03Lv 25:40 Instead, he is to serve with you like a hired servant or traveler who lives with you until the year of jubilee. 
03Lv 25:41 Then he and his children with him may leave to return to his family and his ancestor's inheritance. 
03Lv 25:42 Since they're my servants whom I've brought out from the land of Egypt, they are not to be sold as slaves. 
03Lv 25:43 You are not to rule over them with harshness. You are to fear your God." 39
03Lv 25:44 "As for your male and maid slaves who will be with you, you may buy male and female slaves from among the nations. 
03Lv 25:45 You may also buy from resident aliens who live among you and their families who are with you, whom they fathered in your land. They may become your property.
03Lv 25:46 "You may give them as inherited property to your children after you, to own as properties in perpetuity. You may make bond slaves of them, but no one is to rule over his fellow Israelite with harshness.
03Lv 25:47 "If a resident alien or traveler becomes rich, but your relative who lives next to him is so poor that he sells himself to that resident alien or traveler among you or to a member of the resident alien's family, 
03Lv 25:48 he has the right to be redeemed after he sells himself. One of his brothers may redeem him. 
03Lv 25:49 His uncle or his uncle's son may redeem him or any blood relative from his clan may redeem him. If he becomes rich, then he may redeem himself.
03Lv 25:50 "He is to bring an accounting to the one who bought him, starting from the year he had sold himself until the year of jubilee. The price of his sale is to correspond to the number of years comparable to the time a hired servant stays with him.
03Lv 25:51 "If there are still many years left, he is to refund the cost of his redemption. 
03Lv 25:52 But if only a few years are left until the year of jubilee, he is to bring an accounting of the years that he is to refund for his redemption. 
03Lv 25:53 Like a hired servant, he is to remain with him year after year, but he is not to rule over him with what you see as severity.
03Lv 25:54 "If he isn't redeemed by these, then he is to be set free in the year of jubilee - he and his children with him 
03Lv 25:55 because the Israelites are my servants. They're my servants, since I brought them out of the land of Egypt. I'm the Lord your God."
03Lv 26:1 "You are not to make worthless idols, images, or pillars for yourselves, nor set up for yourselves carved images to bow down to them in the land, because I'm the Lord your God.
03Lv 26:2 "You are to keep my Sabbath and fear my sanctuary. I'm the Lord.
03Lv 26:3 "If you live by my statutes, obey my commands, and observe them, 
03Lv 26:4 then I'll send your rain in its season so that the land will yield its produce and the trees of the field will yield their fruit. 
03Lv 26:5 Threshing will extend to the time of vintage and the vintage will extend to the time of sowing so that you'll eat your bread to your satisfaction and live securely in your land.
03Lv 26:6 "I'll give peace in the land so that you'll lie down without fear. I'll remove wild beasts from the land, not even war will come to your land. 
03Lv 26:7 Instead you'll pursue your enemies and they'll die by the sword before you. 
03Lv 26:8 Five of you will chase a hundred, a hundred of you will chase ten thousand, and your enemies will fall by the sword before you.
03Lv 26:9 "I'll look after you, ensuring that you'll be fruitful. I'll increase your number and keep my covenant with you. 
03Lv 26:10 When you have consumed what was stored of the old, then you'll take out the old and replace it with what's new.
03Lv 26:11 "I'll set up my tabernacle in your midst and I won't loathe you. 
03Lv 26:12 I'll walk among you. I will be your God, and you'll be my people. 
03Lv 26:13 I'm the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt so that you will no longer be their slaves, since I've broken their oppressive yoke upon you to make you walk upright."
03Lv 26:14 "But if you won't listen to me and obey all these commands, 
03Lv 26:15 and if you refuse my statutes, loathe my ordinances, fail to do all my commands, thereby breaching my covenant, 
03Lv 26:16 then I will certainly do this to you£º I'll appoint sudden terror to infect you like tuberculosis and fever. Your the eyes will fail and your life will waste away. You'll plant in vain, because your enemies will consume what you plant.
03Lv 26:17 "I'll set my face against you so that you'll be defeated before your enemies. Those who hate you will have dominion over you and you'll keep fleeing even when no one is pursuing you.
03Lv 26:18 "If despite all of this you still don't listen to me, then I'll punish you seven times more on account of your sins. 
03Lv 26:19 I'll break your mighty pride. I'll make the heavens to be like iron and the ground like bronze. 
03Lv 26:20 Your strength will be spent in vain, because your land won't yield its produce and the trees of the land won't yield its fruit.
03Lv 26:21 "If you live life contrary to me and remain unwilling to listen to me, then I'll add to your wounds seven times more on account of your sins. 
03Lv 26:22 I'll send the wild beasts against you from the open country to deprive you of your children, destroy your cattle, and decrease your number so that your roads become desolate. 
03Lv 26:23 If despite these things you will don't return to me, but live life contrary to me, 
03Lv 26:24 then I'll certainly oppose you. I'll take vengeance against you seven fold on account of your sins. 
03Lv 26:25 I'll bring the sword against you to execute the vengeance of my covenant. When you gather in your cities, I'll send a pestilence. As a result, you'll be delivered into the control of your enemies.
03Lv 26:26 "When I destroy the source of your bread, ten women will bake bread in one oven. Then they'll return back your bread by weight. You'll eat but won't be satisfied. 
