04Nm 30:1 Later, Moses told the elders of the Israelite tribes, "This is what the Lord has commanded. 
04Nm 30:2 When a man makes a vow to the Lord, or swears an oath - an obligation that is binding to himself -  he is not to break his word. Instead, he is to fulfill whatever promise came out of his mouth."
04Nm 30:3 "When a young woman makes a vow to the Lord or pledges herself to an obligation while she still lives in her father's house, 
04Nm 30:4 and her father hears her vow and the obligations that she had pledged herself to fulfill, yet her father keeps silent about it, then all her vows and every obligation she pledged herself to are to stand.
04Nm 30:5 "But if her father disallows her on the same day that he hears what she has said, then all her vows and every obligation she had pledged herself to fulfill are not to stand. The Lord will forgive her, because her father has forbidden her."
04Nm 30:6 "If she has a husband and she makes a vow that is binding on herself, or if she makes a hasty vow with her mouth that she pledges herself to fulfill, 
04Nm 30:7 and husband hears her vow, yet remains silent on the day that he hears is, then her vows are to stand and the obligation to that she had pledged herself to fulfill is to stand. 
04Nm 30:8 But if, on the same day her husband hears, and he disallows her, then he has revoked her vows that she made for herself, along with any hasty vows that she spoke and to which she pledged herself to fulfill. The Lord will forgive her."30
04Nm 30:9 "Everything that a widow or a divorced woman pledges herself to fulfill are to be binding on her. 
04Nm 30:10 But if, while she had been living in her late or former husband's house, she makes a vow or a promise that binds her with an oath, 
04Nm 30:11 and her husband hears it but remains silent, not disallowing it, then all her vows are to stand, along with every obligation that she has pledged herself to fulfill.
04Nm 30:12 "But if her husband disallowed them the very day that he heard her, everything that she spoke relating to her vows and her obligation to herself are not to stand, because her husband had revoked them. The Lord will forgive her.
04Nm 30:13 "Her husband may confirm or revoke every vow and binding obligation that afflicts her. 
04Nm 30:14 But if her husband remains silent about her from day to day, then he has affirmed all her vows or obligations that she has obligated herself to fulfill. He has affirmed them because he remained silent from the day he heard her vows. 
04Nm 30:15 But if had nullified them after he had heard, then he will be responsible for any resulting iniquity."
04Nm 30:16 These are the statutes that the Lord commanded Moses concerning a man and his wife and concerning a father and his young daughter while she still lives in her father's house.
04Nm 31:1 Later, the Lord told Moses, 
