04Nm 31:33 72,000 cattle, 
04Nm 31:34 61,000 donkeys, and 
04Nm 31:35 32,000 women who had not had sexual relations with a man.
04Nm 31:36 Now half of the share of those who went to war numbered 337,500 sheep, 
04Nm 31:37 so the Lord's tribute from the sheep totaled 675.
04Nm 31:38 The cattle numbered 36,000 so the Lord's tribute totaled 72.
04Nm 31:39 The donkeys numbered 30,500 so the Lord's tribute totaled 61.
04Nm 31:40 The people numbered 16,000, and Lord's tribute totaled 32 people.
04Nm 31:41 Then Moses gave the tribute, a raised offering of the Lord, to Eleazar the priest, just as the Lord had commanded Moses. 
04Nm 31:42 From half of the share of the Israelites that Moses had set aside from the soldiers 
04Nm 31:43 there wee 337,500 sheep for the community, 
04Nm 31:44 36,000 cattle, 
04Nm 31:45 30,500 donkeys, 
04Nm 31:46 and 16,000 people.
04Nm 31:47 Moses took a portion drawn from every 50 Israelites, including from both human and animals, and gave them to the Levites who maintained the Lord's tabernacle, just as the Lord had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:48 Then the officers in charge of thousands of soldiers, the captains of thousands, and the captains of hundreds approached Moses 
04Nm 31:49 and told him, "Your servants took a count of the soldiers who were under our authority. We didn't miss a single man. 
04Nm 31:50 We've brought offerings to the Lord from whatever each man found - jewel-encrusted gold, anklets, bracelets, signet rings, earrings, and necklaces to make atonement for ourselves in the Lord's presence."
04Nm 31:51 Then Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from them and everything that was fashioned into jewels. 
04Nm 31:52 The gold for the raised offering that they brought to the Lord totaled 16,750 shekels, 
