04Nm 32:9 When they arrived in the Eshcol Valley and saw the land, they discouraged the Israelites from entering the land that the Lord had given them.8
04Nm 32:10 "That's why the Lord's anger flared up that day and he promised by an oath that 
04Nm 32:11 'Not one of the men who went up from Egypt from 20 years old and above will see the land that I promised to give to their ancestors, that is, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, because none of them followed me whole heartedly, 
04Nm 32:12 except Jephunneh's son Caleb, the Kenizzite, and Nun's son Joshua. They've whole heartedly followed the Lord.'
04Nm 32:13 "The Lord's anger had flared up against Israel so that he made them wander in the wilderness for 40 years until that whole generation, who committed evil in the eyes of the Lord, had died. 
04Nm 32:14 And now, look! You're acting just like your ancestors, like a brood of sinful men, who are incrementally provoking the fierce anger of the Lord against the Israelites. 
04Nm 32:15 If you stop following him, he will once again abandon them in the wilderness. You'll end up destroying this entire people."14
04Nm 32:16 Then they approached him and said, "Here's where we're going to build corrals for our cattle and cities for our families, 
04Nm 32:17 but we will keep ourselves armed and stay ready to go with the Israelites until we've brought them to their own places. Our families intend to live in fortified cities in the presence of the inhabitants of the land, 
04Nm 32:18 but we won't return to our homes until every Israelite has taken possession of each of their inheritances, 
04Nm 32:19 since our inheritance will not be with them across the Jordan River and beyond. Instead, our inheritance is on this side of the Jordan River, facing eastward."
04Nm 32:20 "If you do this," Moses replied to them, "that is, if you equip yourselves for war in the Lord's presence 
04Nm 32:21 and every one of your armed soldiers crosses over the Jordan River in the presence of the Lord until he has dispossessed his enemies ahead of him 
04Nm 32:22 and subjugated the land before him, then afterwards when you return, you'll be able to stand blameless before the Lord and before Israel. This land will then be your possession before the Lord.
04Nm 32:23 "But if you won't do so, look out! You will be sinning against the Lord. Be certain of this, that your sin will catch up to you! 
04Nm 32:24 So after you've built cities for your families and corrals for your cattle, be sure to keep your promises."
04Nm 32:25 Then the Gaddites and Reubenites spoke, "Your servants will do exactly what our master has commanded. 
04Nm 32:26 Our children, wives, flocks, and all our cattle will be settled in the cities of Gilead, 
04Nm 32:27 but every soldier that we've equipped for battle will cross the Jordan River in the presence of the Lord, as our master has spoken."
04Nm 32:28 So Moses instructed Eleazar the priest and Nun's son Joshua, and the officers of the ancestral tribes of the Israelites, 
04Nm 32:29 telling them, "If the Gaddites and Reubenites cross over the Jordan River with you, that is, all of their soldiers who've been equipped for battle in the Lord's presence, so that the land is subjudated right before your eyes, then you are to give them the land of Gilead as their possession. 
04Nm 32:30 But if the armed men don't cross over with you, then they won't have any possession in the land of Canaan."
04Nm 32:31 "We'll do just what the Lord told your servants," the Gaddites and the Reubenites responded. 
04Nm 32:32 "We are to cross over in battle array in the Lord's presence into the land of Canaan, and afterwards the possession of our inheritance will be in this side of the Jordan River."
04Nm 32:33 So Moses gave to the Gaddites, to the Reubenites, and to the half-tribe of Joseph's son Manasseh the kingdom of Sihon, the king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og, the king of Bashan, the whole land with its cities, and even the territories surrounding it. 
