04Nm 35:1 The Lord spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Moab, beside the Jordan River in Jericho. He told him, 
04Nm 35:2 "Instruct the Israelites to set aside a portion of their inheritance for the Levites to live in, along with grazing land surrounding their towns. 
04Nm 35:3 The towns are to be reserved for their dwelling places and the grazing lands are to be reserved for their cattle, livestock, and all their animals.
04Nm 35:4 "The grazing lands that you are to reserve for use by Levites are to extend 1,500 feet from the walls of the town. 
04Nm 35:5 You are to measure from outside the wall of the town on the east side 3,000 feet, on the south side 3,000 feet, on the west side 3,000 feet, and on the north side 3,000 feet, with the town placed at the center. This reserved area is to serve as grazing land for their towns. 
04Nm 35:6 You are to set aside six towns of refuge from the towns that you will be giving to the Levites, where someone who kills a human being may run for shelter. In addition, give them 42 other towns.
04Nm 35:7 "The total number of towns that you are to give to the Levites is to be 48 towns, including grazing lands surrounding these town. 
04Nm 35:8 You are to apportion the towns that you will be giving the Israelites according to the relative size of the tribe. Take a larger portion from those larger in numbers and a lesser portion from those lesser in number. Each is to set aside towns for the Levites proportional to the size of their inheritance that they receive."
04Nm 35:9 Then the Lord told Moses, 
04Nm 35:10 "Tell the Israelites that when they have crossed the Jordan River into the land of Canaan, 
04Nm 35:11 they are to designate some towns of refuge so that anyone who kills someone inadvertently may flee there. 
04Nm 35:12 They are to serve as cities of refuge from a blood avenger in order to keep the inadvertent killer from dying until he has stood trial in the presence of the community. 
04Nm 35:13 You are to set aside six towns of refuge. 
04Nm 35:14 Appoint three towns this side of the Jordan River and three towns in the land of Canaan to serve as the towns of refuge, 
04Nm 35:15 that is, places of refuge for the Israelites, the resident alien, and any travelers among them. Anyone who kills a person inadvertently may flee there."12
04Nm 35:16 "Whoever uses an iron implement to kill someone is to be adjudged a murderer, and that murderer is certainly to be put to death.
04Nm 35:17 "Furthermore, whoever uses a stone implement to kill someone is to be adjudged a murderer, and that murderer is certainly to be put to death.
04Nm 35:18 "Also, whoever uses a wooden implement to kill someone with it is to be adjudged a murderer, and that murderer is certainly to be put to death.
04Nm 35:19 "The blood avenger himself is to execute the murderer. When he meets him, the murderer is to put him to death. 
04Nm 35:20 If the killer shoved him out of hatred, or hurled something at him while waiting in ambush so that he died, 
04Nm 35:21 or if he struck him with his hand out of hatred so that he dies, then the killed is certainly to be put to death for murder. The avenger of blood is to put him to death when he meets him."
04Nm 35:22 "But if he pushed him suddenly without hatred, or had he hurled something in his direction without waiting in ambush, 
04Nm 35:23 or if he hit him with a stone carelessly so that he was fatally injured, though he isn't his enemy and he wasn't seeking to commit evil against him, 
04Nm 35:24 then the community is to judge between the inadvertent killer and the blood avenger, following these ordinances. 
04Nm 35:25 The community is to release the inadvertent killer from the blood avenger and return him to the town of refuge where he had fled. He is to live there until the High Priest dies, who will have anointed him with holy oil.
04Nm 35:26 "But if the inadvertent killer leaves the town of refuge where he had fled 
04Nm 35:27 and the blood avenger finds him outside the town of refuge where he had fled and kills him, the blood avenger is not to be found guilty of murder. 
04Nm 35:28 The inadvertent killer is to live in the town of refuge until the High Priest dies. After the death of the High Priest, the inadvertent killer is to return to the land of his inheritance. 
04Nm 35:29 These are to be the statutes and ordinance for you throughout all your generations, regardless of where you live."
04Nm 35:30 "Every murderer of a human being is to be executed only according to testimony given by multiple witnesses. A single witness is not to result in a death sentence.
04Nm 35:31 "You are to receive no ransom for the life of a killer who is guilty of murder; instead, he is to die. 
04Nm 35:32 You are not to receive payment of a ransom for someone who had fled to a town of refuge but then left to live in his homeland before the death of the high priest.
04Nm 35:33 "You are not to pollute the land where you live, because blood defiles the land, and the land cannot atone for blood that has been spilled on it, except through the blood of the one who spilled it. 
04Nm 35:34 You are not to defile the land where you will be living, because I'm living among you. I am the Lord, who lives in Israel."
